title: Assignment-23
section: GDAL is a software library for raster and geospatial data, PROJ allows a visual representation with coordinates, projections, and transformation, and GEOS is a library for geometry that is a similar to GIS. They allow us to be implemented in R to perform spatial analysis and create approapriate visuals to represent a dataset.
text: GDAL is a software library for raster and geospatial data, PROJ allows a visual representation with coordinates, projections, and transformation, and GEOS is a library for geometry that is a similar to GIS. They allow us to be implemented in R to perform spatial analysis and create approapriate visuals to represent a dataset.
